RIYADH: Members of the Saudi Arabian Scouts Association guided over 3,000 lost pilgrims on the first day ofÂ Eid, Saudi Press Agency reported on Sunday. A total of 3,390 pilgrims of various nationalities were guided by the scouts to their destinations. Of these pilgrims, 1,313 were taken to their camps and 2,077 were given advice and shown the way. More than 110 scouts guided the pilgrims on the tenth of Dhu Al-Hijjah from six sites in Mina where those performing Hajj will spend today and tomorrow.